					"patching_rect" : [ 842.0, 103.0, 760.0, 40.0 ],
					"text" : "Note: a lot of the complexity of this patch is because sfplay cannot be relied upon. The transcription works by playing back the file at high speed, but if sfplay~ can't keep up with buffering from disk it just rudely stops. So we have to test whether it has completed the playback, and if not we slow down the playback speed a little and try again. Sometimes sfplay~ will stop without even reporting a 'playback stopped' bang, so we have to have an additional test for that. Thanks, sfplay~..."
				}

